# (a) Meteorological products: PAR / Tair / H2O / VPD / Wind Speed / Wind Dir / Precipitation are hybrid products
#     PAR/Tair/H2O/VPD/Wind Speed/Wind Dir are merged with nearby sensors as noted. No gaps in PAR Tair or Tsoil. Gaps in others are present
#     PAR: PAR sensor degradation fixed by transfer function between mid-day PAR and nearby PAR stations at WLEF and NTL-LTER
#          Gaps filled with nearby PAR sensor observations or long-term ensemble average for small gaps
#     Tair: 30 m Air temperature combined with nearby observations
#     H2O: Water vapor mixing ratio combined from Vaisala and Licor sensors and filled where available with NTL LTER Woodruff airport observation
#     VPD: Vapor pressure deficit derived from H2O/filled air temperature/filled surface air pressure
#     Windspeed and direction: 30 m wind speed from sonic anemometer and filled where available with Woodruff airport observation
#     Precipitation: Where available gaps filled with NTL LTER Woodruff airport observation
# (b) Flag descriptions of CO2/H/LE:
#     -1 indicates bad or missing value replaced with -999
#     0 indicates good observation
#     1 indicates night ustar less than 0.3 m s-1 (discard data)
#     2 indicates anamolous nighttime SE wind direction (discard data as per Cook et al. 2004 AgForMet)
#     3 indicates conditions 1 and 2 (discard data)
# (c) u* is taken from 30m and a linear fit of preferred wind speed at 30 m based on u_star_flag
#     1 = ustar at 30 m
#     2 = preferred wind speed at 30 m: linearly fit to ustar at 30m (r=0.84)
#     For the true 30m u* see variable ustar_30
# (d) Gap filled NEE based on Desai et al. 2005 AgForMet moving window regression of filled air temperature and PAR to ustar screened NEE
#     Reco derived from nighttime NEE and temperature
#     GPP reported here is the model fit of NEE residual to PAR. For a more data-based GPP used Reco-NEE_Filled
#     NEE_Model is equal to Reco-GPP
